org.team5940.pantry.processing_network.wpilib.systems.encoder_conversion

Class EncoderToMeasurementNodeGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • NodeGroup
      • org.team5940.pantry.processing_network.wpilib.systems.encoder_conversion.EncoderToMeasurementNodeGroup

  • public class EncoderToMeasurementNodeGroup
extends NodeGroup
    Converts the pulses of an encoder to a useful measurement. The measurement can be any unit depending on what the encoder is measuring and the diameter unit. What the encoder is measuring changes if this returns distance, velocity, or acceleration. The Diameter unit changes the distance unit such as feet or meters.

    • Constructor Detail

      • EncoderToMeasurementNodeGroup

        public EncoderToMeasurementNodeGroup(Network network,
                                     Logger logger,
                                     <any> encoderPulsesValueNode,
                                     double pulsesPerRotation,
                                     double diameter)
        This converts the value of an encoder to a distance/velocity. It can be either distance or velocity depending on what encoder value node is inputed.
        Parameters:
        network - This' Network.
        logger - This' logger.
        encoderPulsesValueNode - The ValueNode for an encoder position, velocity, acceleration, or jerk.
        diameter - The diameter of the wheel this encoder is connected to. Could be anything cylindrical. Also this will determine the unit that will be returned for the distance or velocity such as meters or inches or feet.
        pulsesPerRotation - The conversion of pulses of the encoder to the rotation of the wheel. Should be greater than one.
